---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Gear" current="gear">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Gear & Shopping</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">What to take, what to buy, what to decide. Focused on items specific to this tour — you know your general kit.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Bike</h2>

  <div class="gear-category">
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Hardtail MTB frame</div>
        <div class="item-note">Whatever you're riding. Bikepacking bag mounts on frame, seatpost, bars.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Fork — Fox 36 SL (130mm)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Recommended over RockShox SID for reliability on a 5-month tour. FIT4 damper is more forgiving of missed service intervals. Bladder damper in SID can fail catastrophically if undermaintained — bad news in rural Turkey.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Tires — 2.2"+ all-rounder</div>
        <div class="item-note">Something durable and fast-rolling. Maxxis Ardent, Schwalbe Racing Ralph, or Teravail Ehline. Tubeless essential.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-decide">Decide</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Spare folding tire × 1</div>
        <div class="item-note">No MTB tire availability in eastern Turkey or Albania. Carry from the start, ditch in the Dolomites when shops are accessible again.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Fork Maintenance Kit</h2>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <div class="callout-title">Service schedule</div>
    <p><strong>Every 2–3 weeks:</strong> Lower leg service (20 min job). Pull lowers, clean foam rings, refresh oil, wipe stanchions, reassemble.</p>
    <p><strong>~3 months in (Dolomites):</strong> Full damper service at a shop in Bolzano or Brixen.</p>
    <p><strong>Weekly:</strong> Invert bike for 30 seconds to drain oil into foam rings.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="gear-category">
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">200hr service kit (for your fork model)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Dust seals, foam rings, o-rings, sealhead. Specific to fork model and year — order before departure.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Suspension oil — 50ml Fox Gold 20wt (or equivalent)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Small bottle, enough for the whole trip. Decant from a larger bottle into a lightweight container.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Syringe (10ml)</div>
        <div class="item-note">For measuring oil into lowers during service.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Socket for lower leg bolts</div>
        <div class="item-note">Check your fork's bolt size. Usually 10mm hex or Torx T25.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-decide">Check</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Drivetrain Spares</h2>

  <div class="gear-category">
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Spare chain</div>
        <div class="item-note">Carry from the start. Swap at ~2,500km or when stretch gauge says so. The Alps will eat chains.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Chain quick links × 4</div>
        <div class="item-note">Match to your chain speed. Carry extras — they're tiny and invaluable.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Brake pads × 2 spare sets</div>
        <div class="item-note">The Alps will destroy them. Organic or sintered — your choice, but carry matching pads for your calipers.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Derailleur hanger × 1</div>
        <div class="item-note">Frame-specific. Irreplaceable in the field without the right one.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Chain lube</div>
        <div class="item-note">Wet lube for versatility. Small bottle. Restock in the Dolomites.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-buy">Buy</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Sleep System</h2>

  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <div class="callout-title">Assessment</div>
    <p>System works for the full route. Georgia high passes (late May, ~3,300m, possibly -5°C) are the stress point. 
    Wear everything on those nights. Consider a thin CCF pad as ground insulation backup.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="gear-category">
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Big Agnes Fly Creek 1 (~2018)</div>
        <div class="item-note">3-season ultralight. Adequate for the whole route. Not great in high wind — avoid exposed ridgeline camps. Limits: ~0°C comfort, moderate wind tolerance.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Cumulus 350 quilt</div>
        <div class="item-note">Comfort ~2-4°C. Combined with merinos + down jacket → survivable to ~-5°C. Fine for 95% of nights.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Insulated sleeping mat (R~3)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Adequate for three-season. You'll feel ground cold on frozen ground in Georgia. Thin CCF pad underneath would help.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Merino base layers (top + bottom)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Double duty: riding layer and sleep insulation.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Hooded down jacket</div>
        <div class="item-note">Camp insulation and cold night backup. Essential for Georgia and late-season Alps.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Beanie</div>
        <div class="item-note">Merino or fleece. Sleep in it in Georgia and October Alps.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Navigation & Electronics</h2>

  <div class="gear-category">
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Phone with Komoot / Gaia GPS</div>
        <div class="item-note">Primary navigation. Download all regions offline before departure.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Maps.me (offline maps)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Essential backup for Turkey and Balkans. Better POI data than Google Maps offline in rural areas.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Download</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Swiss Mobility app</div>
        <div class="item-note">For Switzerland specifically. Official trail/route network. Free.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Download</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Schengen tracker app</div>
        <div class="item-note">schengen90.app or similar. Log every entry/exit. Non-negotiable.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Download</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Water & Cooking</h2>

  <div class="gear-category">
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Water bottles × 2 (750ml)</div>
        <div class="item-note">Standard cage-mounted bottles.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Soft flask 1-2L</div>
        <div class="item-note">Extra capacity for dry Turkey sections. Rolls up when empty.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-decide">Decide</span>
    </div>
    <div class="gear-item">
      <div>
        <div class="item-name">Stove + fuel</div>
        <div class="item-note">Essential for Georgia, Turkey, Albania wild camping. Gas canisters available in most towns. Optional in the Alps where refugio/town access is frequent.</div>
      </div>
      <span></span>
      <span class="item-status status-own">Own</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Temperature Extremes Reference</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Expected temps</th><th>Concern</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Turkey lowlands (Jul)</td>
        <td>35–43°C day</td>
        <td>Heat management. Ride early/late. Siesta midday.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Kaçkars (Jun, 2,500m+)</td>
        <td>15–25°C day, 5–10°C night</td>
        <td>Pleasant. Afternoon storms.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Albania valleys (Aug)</td>
        <td>35–38°C</td>
        <td>Hot. Stay in mountains where possible.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Georgia passes (late May, 3,300m)</td>
        <td>5–15°C day, -5 to 0°C night</td>
        <td>Coldest nights of the trip. Snow possible. Wear everything.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Dolomites (mid-Sep)</td>
        <td>10–20°C day, 2–8°C night</td>
        <td>Ideal. Autumn colours starting.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Swiss/French Alps (Oct, 2,000m+)</td>
        <td>5–15°C day, -3 to 5°C night</td>
        <td>First snow possible mid-Oct at 2,500m+. Monitor forecasts.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>TNR sections (Oct, 2,300-2,500m)</td>
        <td>3–12°C day, -3 to 3°C night</td>
        <td>At the edge. Have bail-out for each high section.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

</Layout>
